Notes from Arnaud: Longevity. This is a parameter that can easily be obtained from FishBase/SeaLifeBase
Instantaneous growth rate at small size. This is a parameter that can easily be obtained from FishBase/SeaLifeBase
Maximum size. This is a parameter that can easily be obtained from FishBase/SeaLifeBase
Theoretical age of zero length. This is a parameter that can easily be obtained from FishBase/SeaLifeBase
Constant of proportionality of the allometric length-weight relationship. This is a parameter that can easily be obtained from FishBase/SeaLifeBase
Exponent of the allometric length-weight relationship. This is a parameter that can easily be obtained from FishBase/SeaLifeBase
Size at sexual maturity. This is a parameter that can easily be obtained from FishBase/SeaLifeBase
Age at sexual maturity. This is a parameter that can easily be obtained from FishBase/SeaLifeBase to my mind. Please have a look at jhpoelen/fb-osmose-bridge#15
Threshold age below which a linear growth model is used to calculate mean length increase. This is a parameter that could easily be obtained from FishBase/SeaLifeBase to my mind

Length-weight relationship estimated for total lengths (TLs)?: Boolean variable. This is a parameter that I created for the OSMOSE-WFS model but which will undoubtedly be useful for other OSMOSE applications. This parameter could easily be obtained from queries in FishBase/SeaLifeBase to my mind
Annual number of eggs per gram of mature female. This is a parameter that could easily be obtained from queries in FishBase/SeaLifeBase to my mind
Female:male sex ratio. This is a parameter that could easily be obtained from queries in FishBase/SeaLifeBase to my mind

Maximum annual ingestion rate expressed in grams of food per gram of individual and per year. This parameter is usually set to 3.5 g of food per g of individual and per year for all focal functional groups in OSMOSE models. It is similar to Ecopath's Q/B parameter. This parameter could easily be obtained from queries in FishBase/SeaLifeBase to my mind

Critical predation efficiency. This parameter is usually set to 0.57 for all focal functional groups in OSMOSE models. This is a parameter that could possibly be obtained from queries in FishBase/SeaLifeBase to my mind

Maximum annual starvation mortality. This parameter is usually set to 0.3 year-1 for all focal functional groups in OSMOSE models.This is a parameter that could possibly be obtained from queries in FishBase/SeaLifeBase to my mind

Predator/prey size ratios defined for juveniles (immature individuals) and adults (mature individuals) of each focal functional group. NB: the predator/prey size ratios of juveniles and adults of a given focal functional group can be identical if this makes sense from an ecological standpoint. These are parameters that could possibly be obtained from queries in FishBase/SeaLifeBase to my mind

Body size threshold that separates the predator/prey size ratio for juvenile individuals and the predator/prey size ratio for adult individuals. This is a parameter that can easily be obtained from FishBase/SeaLifeBase
matrix of the accessibility coefficients of life stages of focal functional groups to each other. This is a parameter that could possibly be obtained from queries in FishBase/SeaLifeBase to my mind
Age threshold that separates the accessibility coefficients of the life stages of the focal functional group of interest
